      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:29:4",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " إِذَا قَذَفَ الرَّجُلُ امْرَأَتَهُ ثُمَّ أَكْذَبَ نَفْسَهُ جُلِدَ الْحَدَّ وَ كَانَتِ امْرَأَتَهُ وَ إِنْ لَمْ يُكْذِبْ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ تَلَاعَنَا وَ يُفَرَّقُ بَيْنَهُمَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, form Yunus, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘When the man accuses his wife, then admits having lied to himself, would be whipped the Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>), and she would be his wife; but if he did not admit lying to himself, there would be cursing and separation between the two of them’."
        ]
      }
    }
